===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|poudre||lang=enm}}, {{term|pouldre||lang=enm}}, {{etyl|fro}} {{term|poudre||lang=fro}}, {{term|poldre||lang=fro}}, {{term|puldre||lang=fro}}, {{etyl|la}} {{term|pulvis||lang=la|dust, powder}}. compare [[pollen]] fine flour, mill dust, E. pollen. Compare [[polverine]], [[pulverize]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/paʊ.də(ɹ)/}}
* {{audio|en-us-powder.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|aʊdə(ɹ)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|-}}

# The fine particles to which any dry substance is reduced by pounding, grinding, or triturating, or into which it falls by decay; dust.
#* {{rfdate}} [[w:William Shakespeare|William Shakespeare]]:
#*: Grind their bones to '''powder''' small.
# An explosive mixture used in gunnery, blasting, etc.; [[gunpowder]].
# {{informal}} Light, dry, fluffy [[snow]].

